# Empirical Strategy

### Static model

Consider the following model in first differences

\begin{equation*}
	\Delta \ln y_{ict} = \delta_t + 
	\beta \Delta \ln \underline{w}_{ict} + 
	\Delta \mathbf{X}^{'}_{ct} \eta + 
	\Delta \varepsilon_{ict}
\end{equation*}

where:

- $y_{ict}$ our main outcome variable, rents per square foot 
- ZIP code $i$ 
- county $c$ 
- month $t$ 
- $\delta_t$ month fixed effects
- $\mathbf{X}_{ct}$ is a vector of county-level controls. 

### Dynamic models

\begin{equation}
	\Delta \ln y_{ict} = \delta_t + 
	\sum_{r=-s}^{s} \beta_r \Delta \ln \underline{w}_{ic,t+r} + 
	\Delta \mathbf{X}^{'}_{ct}\eta + 
	\Delta \varepsilon_{ict}
\end{equation}

-$\{\beta_r\}_{r=-s}^{s}$ are dynamic effects of leads and lags of the minimum wage 

Advantages of this specification:

- Test for pre-trends
- Assess dynamics of the effect


