### Identification

Identifying assumption: strict exogeneity conditional on controls and fixed effects

\begin{equation*}
	E[\Delta \varepsilon_{ict} \Delta \ln \underline{w}_{ic\tau}  
							| \alpha_i, \delta_t, \Delta \mathbf{X}_{ct}] = 0
	\ \ \ \forall \tau \in \{\underline{T}, \overline{T} \}
\end{equation*}

-- 

Conditional on controls, the unobserved shocks to rents are uncorrelated with past and present values of minimum wage changes

### Threats to Identification

- State of the economy correlated both with rents and MW changes 

--

We control for employment, average wages, and establishment counts of sectors of the economy that have very few MW workers: 

- Financial sector
- IT
- Business Services

--

- Anticipatory effects from landlords and/or renters

--

  - We check if there are housing supply responses to MW changes and we find no effect
  - We test for pretrends ahead of MW changes and we do not detect them

