### Checks

- Identification
  - Pretrends tests $\to$ dynamics consistent with a causal effect
  - Check effects of MW on housing supply $\to$ We find nothing
  - Allowing for feedback (Arellano-Bond) $\to$ sequential exogeneity (weaker identifying assumption)
  - Use the whole rents data (fully unbalanced panel) $\to$ late entrant zipcodes have same dynamics
  - Use only data from July 2015 and on (fully balanced panel) $\to$ entry of zipcodes to sample not correlated with MW changes
  - Change economic control sets $\to$ results not driven by controlling for particular economic shocks
  - Allow for zipcode level heterogeneity in time paths $\to$ results not driven by time paths differences between treated and untreated units

- External Validity
    - Reweighting data to match main urban areas
    
- Assesing the magnitude of the effects
  - Use QCEW data to estimate effect of MW on average wage income $\to$ pass-through from MW to rents around $20\%$
  - Use estimates from the literature $\to$ pass-through from MW to rents from $22\%$ to $28\%$

